Good Cotton Harvest in Central China 
Total cotton output in central China's Hunan province is expected to
hit a record high this year, at 240,000 tons.
The acreage planted in cotton has doubled the 1989's figure and
increased to 200,000 hectares. The province has become a cotton
exporter.
The province started a high-quality hybrid cotton project at the
beginning of the year and more than 100,000 ha of land has been planted
in the hybrid cotton, with per hectare yield of 1,500 kilograms.
